title: Unemployment rate in Turkey 2019
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Unemployment rate. In total the number of data points it has is 21.
Overall Unemployment rate has increased over the Year.
The most drastic increase took place within the Year 2008 and 2009.
The highest Unemployment rate, of value 12.55 was reached at Year 2009
The lowest Unemployment rate, of value 6.5 was reported at Year 2000
